<body>
    <h1>Golden Path - Web Microservice Framework</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"013666c209bb"></p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"5ec003eb-420e-4610-9283-dc068a8154c5">
<p local-id=3D"bac9b63e85cf">A standard for any new API, Webhook, and Event=
-Driven services across ecoATM.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"4d7d10bd-4e3c-4d8a-a6d9-5bc16f994743">
<h2 local-id=3D"62f108d4ecaa" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Cor=
eConcepts">Core Concepts</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"3=
97e4cc7-bbf6-4568-9c57-4e2602bbd5b8" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bde19ca4-e306-4469-9daf-4237b6aaed49">
<th data-local-id=3D"ac455ff9-8cfc-491e-ae30-5123f05c92c8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"4944cbb530cc">Principle</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"31e4bb35-f88d-47ae-b400-f467e2030d1d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"76931b04a19d">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9f73f9be-7553-468f-82cb-3c53d54569cf">
<td data-local-id=3D"40f2e97d-5ef7-49dd-b9d6-bd2956d524f2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5beb02071359"><strong>Containerized Applications</strong></p=
></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"09a10eb3-087f-4ccb-916d-27088b8e0590" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ffb4b8b18966"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"6598f171-b2c5-48cc-b0c8-64bdeb1f1bbf">All applications should be run wi=
thin a container</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2b0a3777-8350-43c7-8eb7-fbaf475051d9">
<td data-local-id=3D"0ef6af60-f303-4cab-a444-7f8eae2c21a3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fee348952f53"><strong>Language Agnostic</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"51c4564e-0c83-4dca-ab8b-8890579efb02" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1a54ef3f529f">Architecture is universal for all programming =
languages</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"919102d6-2db3-402b-ba56-cbca07030043">
<td data-local-id=3D"1ff7ef5d-3d5f-4b27-84b0-efd517d7da45" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ab5f92909a2b"><strong>Decoupled and Extensible</strong></p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"176e0163-e4a4-43b4-bf85-7dc41897ac85" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6c09a13cad8a">Each piece of the architecture should have min=
imal impact on each other</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3172ad5e-b9d5-45e5-b20e-ff4b4ee60929">
<td data-local-id=3D"8cb2d5bc-e27e-4e01-8f1d-5fb5d1551cf3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9c9640c494e0"><strong>Plug &amp; Play</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"304d44c6-735e-4733-a4a2-158a9622f165" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"00d9b651a8b7">Changing downstream integrations should not im=
pact upstream ones</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d58e48ba-5217-44f5-bf03-cf2c25978169">
<td data-local-id=3D"7ccbbc4a-2a56-462a-8ad3-b4ab54a102b1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c4b112639aa"><strong>Observable by Default</strong></p></td=
>
<td data-local-id=3D"8e6b79ee-730c-4f73-914e-b96c3847beda" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2a0ec2bd9a3">All services must emit logs, traces, and metri=
cs without additional developer configuration. Observability is not optiona=
l =E2=80=94 it is enforced via the Datadog base image and agent.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d0f20e4c-d49f-4754-9544-b15e9061ef7a">
<td data-local-id=3D"143569c8-2421-4fc1-a9dc-f42af5559c84" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94d1146e645d"><strong>ARB-Governed</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"63835628-b178-4c46-8b72-5650132e7f1c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"41f6af050152">Changes that qualify as Tier 1 under the SDLC =
require Architecture Review Board (ARB) approval before build begins. Servi=
ces built on golden paths do not require ARB review.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"83e7b250-9b99-4a59-a390-8b12e5183b2d">
<h2 local-id=3D"93831a5c1ed7" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Key=
ArchitecturalDesign"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"c642=
e81b-df62-4248-b62b-c90dcf1ef1dd">Key Architectural Design</span></h2>
<div style=3D"width: 100.0%;display: block;text-align: center;">
<img src=3D"https://atl-embed.lucid.app/api/confluence/lucidchart/documents=
/f104db75-2500-44f5-8662-e63cfcdf87cd/embeds/ef836ea7-c444-4a4e-81c0-434bfe=
d97aa0/pages/1?jwt=3DeyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJDb25mbHVlbmNlOjMwMDA0N=
TIyMjIiLCJpYXQiOjE3NzYyMDExMDUsImV4cCI6MTc3NjIwMTE2NSwicXNoIjoiYzc0MDRmZWMw=
ZDdmYWEwMmVlMjNmYmU3YmI0ZDNhYmNhNTQxNGQ4YWZhNDcwODZjOGY5YTI3MTMzNWUyNzhkOSJ=
9.e7enZSsv3f-cKzkYLeLTw0YdlyOrKec9VHdd6xgnN24" alt=3D"API Framework" title=
=3D"API Framework" style=3D"max-width: 100.0%;">
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"0c5522f9-d659-4d87-accd-919776d27f44">
<h2 local-id=3D"31b727b2ef02" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Ent=
rypoint"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"f413135a-a2f9-42=
bf-8ff7-226796c7cb8f">Entrypoint</span></h2>
<p local-id=3D"f70f311392ca">The top-level URL for all REST and GraphQL ope=
rations is <code>https://api.ecoatm.com</code>. This provides a single entr=
y point to the entire API catalog, supported by <strong>AWS API Gateway</st=
rong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f92a2e7d7dc6">Endpoints are secured by a token-based authent=
ication scheme. Authorization is handled by decoding tokens to determine th=
e privileges of authenticated requests and assigning the proper IAM policie=
s. This ensures that individual applications do not need to handle their ow=
n authorization =E2=80=94 it is controlled at a gateway/infrastructure leve=
l.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b730b554d3e8">All applications should be built such that the=
y can eventually become publicly facing with minimal rework.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0b1d4375a4b8">The top-level API Gateway contains:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bd7ea2e7-5e75-4342-bdf3-e27ffe59ddb3">
<li local-id=3D"93c11429-4eed-42d0-8c2d-a1e86ce690f8">
<p local-id=3D"58e9077e4850">Base authentication routes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"49e1427e-2c1c-40e7-a4ed-d8ee7dabf768">
<p local-id=3D"6f2b617e7994">Directories that map to collection-level gatew=
ays</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2f1527b9-ab9a-4c47-9fea-f92610ccd042">
<p local-id=3D"754c5169fbae">Individual GraphQL endpoints per service, moun=
ted within their respective collection paths</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"f66a5b8b-e251-49a8-b99b-fcafc59c7b04">
<h2 local-id=3D"30792ca51155" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Col=
lections">Collections</h2>
<p local-id=3D"4c95460d17f0">A <strong>collection</strong> represents a gro=
up of microservices that operate in the same functional area, linked by a c=
ommon collection-level API Gateway. The root (<code>/</code>) of the collec=
tion-level gateway maps to a directory of the top-level gateway. For exampl=
e, a pricing collection would map its route to <code>api.ecoatm.com/pricing=
</code>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0297044d4915"><strong>Collection boundaries should align wit=
h domain/business capability boundaries, not team or org chart boundaries.<=
/strong> Organizing collections around team structure rather than business =
domains is the most common source of coupling problems in microservice arch=
itectures.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7797fb426ca4">Each collection must have a <strong><span clas=
s=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"7339e191-37d6-4e05-bf99-9494dc8fc34=
7">designated owning team</span></strong>. Ownership should be registered a=
nd visible. This feeds directly into the ARB and SDLC processes =E2=80=94 t=
he "who approves what" question is only answerable when collection ownershi=
p is explicit.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5ea5c18ad31e">*<strong>Note: revisit later as teams become m=
ore self-sufficient</strong></p>
<hr local-id=3D"07893867-3a6d-4857-a6bf-bdde518b632f">
<h2 local-id=3D"6128a997e2f0" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Ver=
sioning">Versioning</h2>
<p local-id=3D"50a03098c4df">Routes <strong>must</strong> contain a version=
 identifier for all endpoint. For example, version 1 of the pricing engine =
is at:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">api.eco=
atm.com/pricing/v1</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d469a1c88c67">Unversioned APIs create breaking change risk w=
ith no notice to consumers.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"36bb3a87d69d" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Dep=
recationPolicy">Deprecation Policy</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6e6be860ab08">A version must have a defined support window b=
efore it can be sunset:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"35350229-2ce3-4a49-9f8e-39a8ba24c91f">
<li local-id=3D"8b69c22d-ff5a-467d-8145-de120d98af87">
<p local-id=3D"116560535c3f"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"0823e5f4-eaf0-476f-ad0a-64a0e687d151">A minimum </span><strong>3-month =
deprecation notice</strong> is required before removing a version.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0102f7b8-fab7-4750-b290-842be6d678d7">
<p local-id=3D"3afae4d46401">Deprecations must be communicated via changelo=
g entry and surface in the OpenAPI spec.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3a3abab9-3f03-4d6c-8cec-4e9aed179235">
<p local-id=3D"43b1e406d6d3">Deprecated versions should return a <code>Depr=
ecation</code> header in responses pointing to the replacement.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"ef666f38-b622-4257-bb16-5f5ebf3f3de2">
<h2 local-id=3D"d640a593ffb2" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-App=
licationLayer">Application Layer</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b4ea93fd30c7">The application layer consists of a combinatio=
n of <strong>Lambdas</strong>, and <strong>EKS deployments</strong>. The ex=
pectation is that the majority of applications will consist of one or more =
Lambdas.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d1f623ede02f" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Lam=
bda(Default)">Lambda (Default)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4e1b0131563e">Lambdas are the default compute unit for both =
<strong>request/response</strong> and <strong>event-driven</strong> workloa=
ds:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"88d23874-dc9a-4244-b333-9c3f193ea29e">
<li local-id=3D"0c071cde-b659-47f4-9e91-d32a9b0418ad">
<p local-id=3D"8d0be8c2b938">For <strong>HTTP APIs</strong>, a Lambda shoul=
d map to one route and one HTTP method (e.g., <code>GET /pricing/v1/quote</=
code>). This keeps the scope of each deployment unit narrow and business lo=
gic minimal per function.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a6c06073-e802-4509-b55e-d188db80f274">
<p local-id=3D"437e9a8be62f">For <strong>event-driven workloads</strong>, a=
 Lambda should map to one event source (e.g., one MSK consumer group, one S=
NS subscription). The same single-responsibility principle applies.</p></li=
>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f838ffc65fe0"><strong>Cold start guidance:</strong> Cold sta=
rt latency must be factored into SLO definitions for customer-facing endpoi=
nts. Cold starts are generally less critical for async event consumers wher=
e strict latency SLOs are not required, but should still be documented. For=
 critical systems that require low-latency, consider using provisioned conc=
urrency.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"51419bab8401" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-EKS=
">EKS</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ef49cc4b9f16">EKS should be used when a Lambda may be inappr=
opriate, such as cost, strong latency requirements, runtime limitations (&g=
t;=3D 15 minute execution time).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"828a142b3724" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Con=
tainerRequirements">Container Requirements</h3>
<p local-id=3D"cc7112a23f70">All applications and services must be built as=
 <strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"d041a82d-4979-4d=
f3-a3de-a83d36efce21">Docker images</span></strong> and deployed as contain=
ers. This ensures portability and language agnosticism. The image defines i=
ts own runtime environment, removing any dependency on specific underlying =
infrastructure.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"a722032c1184" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Alt=
ernativeInfrastructure">Alternative Infrastructure</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8c37f12e173a">As an ARB, we decided against frameworks such =
as ECS and Fargate tasks to minimize complexity. We are also looking to mov=
e away from EC2 for application deployments.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"237ec26b-1126-444e-ae8e-5200b1ca06f6">
<h2 local-id=3D"af16ca46539d" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Com=
monLibraries=E2=80=94IntegrationLayer">Common Libraries =E2=80=94 Integrati=
on Layer</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1b113cad12d9">Data and vendor integrations should be abstrac=
ted as <strong>common libraries</strong> implementing the required function=
ality. This allows downstream integrations to change freely without impacti=
ng business logic upstream (Plug &amp; Play). For example, switching from <=
code>Communication Tool X</code> to <code>Communication Tool Y</code> shoul=
d be scoped entirely to the library =E2=80=94 consuming services should onl=
y need to update their dependency version.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"04df73bebde0" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Lib=
raryGovernance">Library Governance</h3>
<p local-id=3D"70ba7ac1be22">Common libraries carry architectural risk beca=
use a breaking change in a library can affect N upstream consumers simultan=
eously. The following rules apply:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7c4a7e2a-c003-48b6-b481-2db9f7c2a10f">
<li local-id=3D"d273fc0d-4fbb-4e68-8270-ffbc07a54468">
<p local-id=3D"8a10347f6b61">Libraries must be <strong>versioned</strong> a=
nd published to a private registry (Artifactory).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6ad3ce67-019e-45a9-a24d-f1567d073731">
<p local-id=3D"e4447603d195"><strong>Breaking changes</strong> to a common =
library should be evaluated against the SDLC Tier 1 triggers. If a breaking=
 change meets a trigger (e.g., cross-domain API contract, data flow directi=
on change), it requires ARB review before proceeding.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"807804d6-3bc1-4cb7-a662-15a8acee30a3">
<p local-id=3D"7be5bb9f288f">Each library must have a <strong>designated ow=
ner</strong> =E2=80=94 the same ownership model as collections.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f1749fba-05d7-4f3d-a254-0bfaca0a876b">
<p local-id=3D"a7bdbc691d28">Libraries must follow semantic versioning (<co=
de>MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH</code>) with a changelog.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"a83a887d-0ee9-46cd-916f-861a809d96e4">
<h2 local-id=3D"5913a9d2cc9a" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Dev=
elopmentLifecycle">Development Lifecycle</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b1c97fc0edf0">All services built within this framework must =
follow the <strong>ecoATM Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC)</strong>. =
The microservice framework defines <em>how</em> to build services; the SDLC=
 defines <em>when and how to govern</em> that build process.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c7141de0-f261-43f2-b86e-cbbadc81e903">
<li local-id=3D"3fb207d7-602b-4735-96c1-27bbe973f3bc">
<p local-id=3D"f1c6ec95ad08"><strong>Tier 1 changes</strong> (new services,=
 significant architectural changes) require <strong>ARB approval</strong> b=
efore implementation begins.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c786ddfa-6343-4de2-9469-73c011b1c65f">
<p local-id=3D"e17a5d310c58">Significant changes to collection boundaries a=
re always Tier 1.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8ab73daa-4dc1-4943-bda7-328e64e29375">
<p local-id=3D"8bcb68c74235">New event-driven systems, new event backbone c=
omponents (topics, queues, buses), and new event schemas are always Tier 1 =
=E2=80=94 they establish contracts between services and are difficult to ch=
ange after consumers have been built against them.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"981accf7-d117-44af-8b2c-c81977c70c71">
<h2 local-id=3D"b78ef2c2c039" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Com=
monDownstreamIntegrations">Common Downstream Integrations</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"5f7137eb26b7" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Dat=
adog">Datadog</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6bd872fcf9d5">All monitoring at ecoATM is handled by Datadog=
. All applications within the Microservice framework must send logs, traces=
, and monitoring data to Datadog.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6ff61b90-cb19-431c-8539-dd127dc06466">
<li local-id=3D"172ab7bc-9dfe-45ea-a7a6-43489129b3da">
<p local-id=3D"4b7c470293f1">The <strong>base image for all Lambdas</strong=
> must contain the Datadog Lambda handler, ensuring any new Lambda automati=
cally emits data to Datadog.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4658d9d21318"><strong>*Note: </strong>We will begin to migra=
te to using OpenTelemetry instead of proprietary Datadog integration, and s=
hould prioritize a migration for lambdas.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c096ab7af01e" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Swa=
gger/OpenAPI">Swagger / OpenAPI</h3>
<p local-id=3D"98a3f4757b6a">All REST applications must have <strong>OpenAP=
I specification</strong>. <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://stopli=
ght.io/" rel=3D"nofollow"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D=
"0a088448-a71c-4340-a692-a39f70a6f344">Stoplight.io</span></a><span class=
=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"0a088448-a71c-4340-a692-a39f70a6f344=
"> </span>consumes these to provide an endpoint catalog.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ff17adbf-523a-4ef7-bc90-7232a2f49c14">
<li local-id=3D"88da3e4c-03da-4bca-842b-c71d713c645b">
<p local-id=3D"319c3c45591c">Specs must be <strong>committed to the reposit=
ory</strong> (not generated only at runtime) so they are reviewable as part=
 of a pull request.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f34884bf-3b5c-4ee7-bd10-6e8a5484a859">
<p local-id=3D"5a17fbbfb2a1">Specs must be <strong>validated in CI</strong>=
 using a schema linter (e.g., <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://st=
oplight.io/open-source/spectral" rel=3D"nofollow">Spectral</a>). A broken o=
r outdated spec is worse than no spec =E2=80=94 it produces incorrect docum=
entation and misleads consumers.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"82c4c4143e63" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Asy=
ncAPI">AsyncAPI</h3>
<p local-id=3D"08c0167df0bf"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www=
.asyncapi.com/" rel=3D"nofollow">AsyncAPI</a> is the event-driven equivalen=
t of OpenAPI =E2=80=94 it describes channels, message schemas, and producer=
/consumer bindings in a machine-readable format. It is the intended long-te=
rm standard for documenting event-driven services at ecoATM.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2bd9228a345f">AsyncAPI is not currently mandated as our API =
catalog tooling (Stoplight) does not support it. Event contracts should be =
documented in the service's README until tooling support is available. Asyn=
cAPI will be revisited as a formal requirement if tooling changes.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"550437936e32" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Gra=
phQL">GraphQL</h3>
<p local-id=3D"53b039e3fee4">Services that expose a GraphQL API do so as in=
dividual endpoints mounted within their collection path (e.g., <code>api.ec=
oatm.com/pricing/graphql</code>). There is no shared supergraph at this tim=
e. Use of GraphQL should be discussed with Architecture before new services=
 are onboarded as our preference should be to use REST.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d6eafb3711ec">GraphQL endpoints are subject to the same gate=
way-level authentication requirements as REST endpoints. Versioning works d=
ifferently from REST =E2=80=94 the endpoint itself is not versioned. Instea=
d, the schema evolves through field-level changes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"df667630-cca6-490a-9059-67235a2d57d1">
<li local-id=3D"2d0fc235-8d3a-4657-9227-b4d1967ffa85">
<p local-id=3D"71a82e721b1a">New fields may be added freely as they are non=
-breaking.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9b651e5a-d1a1-4c71-aff2-bd51730cfdcc">
<p local-id=3D"a3335941672b">Fields should be marked <code>@deprecated</cod=
e> with a reason before removal, giving consumers time to migrate.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7ea6b996-be0e-47a7-a1c9-690023ebf646">
<p local-id=3D"d75aeb23e8ce">Removing or renaming a field without deprecati=
on is a breaking change and must be avoided.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b8267405d3ab">A future consolidation into a federated graph =
may be evaluated as GraphQL coverage matures across the platform.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"bbf5c058-b406-40a7-b621-2cab2c3978dd">
<h2 local-id=3D"9c009ca0b9b9" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Eve=
nt-DrivenArchitecture">Event-Driven Architecture</h2>
<div style=3D"width: 100.0%;display: block;text-align: center;">
<img src=3D"https://atl-embed.lucid.app/api/confluence/lucidchart/documents=
/f104db75-2500-44f5-8662-e63cfcdf87cd/embeds/0b587cd0-f1a1-4365-8b88-fe3c05=
11cd36/pages/3?jwt=3DeyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJDb25mbHVlbmNlOjMwMDA0N=
TIyMjIiLCJpYXQiOjE3NzYyMDExMDUsImV4cCI6MTc3NjIwMTE2NSwicXNoIjoiNzk0OWVkYzAz=
OWEzODk3YTdiY2M4OWU2NzIyNjBjYThmZjg5M2JjODgyZTFkNTMzYmY1MzdhOTU0YzliYjNjNiJ=
9.GcbwzIMSijEOfBkFpThxtSeny0r1aHriDJ7YMsu2plY" alt=3D"API Framework" title=
=3D"API Framework" style=3D"max-width: 100.0%;">
</div>
<p local-id=3D"9a54239a3011">Event-driven architecture (EDA) is the pattern=
 for services that communicate <strong>asynchronously</strong> through even=
ts rather than synchronous request/response. EDA is the right model when:</=
p>
<ul local-id=3D"3f6e365c-94b9-4744-af40-70a94dd089dd">
<li local-id=3D"68fbbe54-adcc-44c3-a5dd-10669a9b0625">
<p local-id=3D"6b41443f9771">The producer does not need to wait for the res=
ult of downstream processing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d7b5fac7-a9a3-46f4-b97a-67b05cae8d8f">
<p local-id=3D"0e26e4fbb433">Multiple consumers need to react to the same o=
ccurrence independently</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e258f756-1b4e-43fd-8ab5-9da4f5b017f0">
<p local-id=3D"b8f3d7d3573b">Services in different domains need to remain d=
ecoupled across their lifecycles</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3616de00-5cfc-4478-b6c8-007b45ce4aca">
<p local-id=3D"5a02e870e932">Work needs to be buffered, retried, or process=
ed at variable rates</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b73b199e059d">EDA and REST/HTTP APIs are <strong>complementa=
ry</strong>, not alternatives. Most systems will use both: HTTP for synchro=
nous, user-facing or query operations; events for state changes, integratio=
ns, and background processing.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"43d1e381740b" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Bro=
kerSelection">Broker Selection</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e59a8580299d">ecoATM operates three event brokers. Each has =
a defined role =E2=80=94 new services should use the appropriate broker for=
 their use case rather than treating them as interchangeable.</p>
<p local-id=3D"22bca3f78166"><strong>AWS IoT Core</strong> is the entry poi=
nt for all device-originated events. From a microservice perspective it is =
a source, not a system to integrate with directly =E2=80=94 backend service=
s consume device events from MSK, not from IoT Core.</p>
<p local-id=3D"17b869fa2b2f"><strong>Amazon MSK (Kafka)</strong> is the pri=
mary event streaming backbone for service-to-service communication. It is t=
he right choice when you need durable, replayable, ordered event streams or=
 high-throughput pipelines. For topic design, consumer patterns, schema reg=
istry, naming conventions, and IaC standards, refer to the <strong>MSK Arch=
itectural Pattern</strong> document.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a9ed560684b7"><strong>Amazon SNS + SQS</strong> is appropria=
te for lightweight, lower-volume async integration where Kafka's durability=
 and replay characteristics are not required =E2=80=94 simple fan-out, noti=
fication triggers, or decoupling two services without needing a full stream=
ing pipeline.</p>
<p local-id=3D"23079fa0d76b">When in doubt between MSK and SNS/SQS, prefer =
MSK. Consolidating on fewer brokers reduces operational complexity and keep=
s the event model consistent across the platform.</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"1bcb62e1-d89c-457c-9a18-3ce4d7cd1691">
<p local-id=3D"2b55f049d634"><strong>Note:</strong> Amazon EventBridge is n=
ot a standard ecoATM broker outside of running cron jobs. It may be used se=
lectively for SaaS integrations or for bridging MSK events to specific targ=
ets =E2=80=94 consult with Architecture before introducing it.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 local-id=3D"88719cd38d9e" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Eve=
ntDesignStandards">Event Design Standards</h3>
<p local-id=3D"964f7447b64f">Events are contracts. Once a consumer is built=
 against an event schema, changes are a breaking change for that consumer. =
Design events carefully up front.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ada9cc452d6c"><strong>Naming convention:</strong> Events sho=
uld be named in past tense to reflect that they describe something that has=
 already occurred:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{domain=
}.{entity}.{past-tense-verb}
# Examples:
pricing.quote.requested
order.transaction.completed
device.kiosk.checked-in
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d587a484d81f"><strong>Standard event envelope:</strong> All =
events must include the following standard metadata envelope alongside the =
business payload:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c=
59fb246-1486-4367-9eff-46f9d88eebc4" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4e5f9beb-a573-492c-968c-c2b16ad9f179">
<th data-local-id=3D"2829ab29-28b5-4493-b171-eaef04edd1e1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"245cee9c0a78">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"fc148769-435d-4172-9bf5-c47d1b0e2ab0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cfcd26230f9a">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"92df6c83-6dcf-4a7b-bc07-4d26dccdb88f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a931d234133b">Required</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"305ace1f-e643-48d6-be27-573e96453487" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"450a6acb37d8">Example</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e309c162-058a-4dbf-9055-3711bcdeb85f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6453776522be">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"25d29935-f42c-4fb0-a066-260d66e2bb00">
<td data-local-id=3D"e658b1c7-a75e-41f0-b292-7d3b5337c1f6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7f5e621c73dc"><code>eventId</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"12712cc4-b89a-424b-9321-a6129f9df7ac" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"735ce61a21be">string (UUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f6f629fc-34e3-4a69-bf35-941f45f81271" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"13d9f36f625b">Yes =E2=80=94 generated by MSK</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8be43edd-54be-4565-8079-9118aaa374bc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b2445b2490b"><code>"a1b2-c3d4..."</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0003403d-08e2-4375-9c6f-e9420a2fb654" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"165a782e5b8c">Globally unique identifier for this event inst=
ance</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c2c6b4dc-4720-43c9-866d-f422f141d9ce">
<td data-local-id=3D"150e9cfb-3ce8-4995-9766-3095587a4075" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ed7429760859"><code>eventVersion</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8b8ff80a-6809-49d3-84ae-258e540583e3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0f229cdc9081">string (SemVer)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"99d4c7a8-fe51-43ce-b1e1-3b375cdc74ad" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa067df031dd">Yes =E2=80=94 generated by MSK</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"99842f68-6047-4b05-a15c-4979705b008e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d3c3e0638498"><code>"1.0.0"</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7111cfa5-3bca-4254-9f59-74d46e4d743d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2839c3e0562f">Version of this event schema</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"138ec3cc-5468-4633-9239-cf10bda0dad2">
<td data-local-id=3D"fd4e1d96-c1c2-454a-b226-a46fc8569411" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fe2536055e33"><code>timestamp</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0df88a6e-762d-45b9-8659-860e988f604c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9a9f9a3720c9">string (ISO-8601)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"84296438-0b0d-4973-887f-fdc86b69c9ea" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2cc9cc30bb97">Yes =E2=80=94 generated by MSK</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"92dbe782-8e32-4e0d-bfba-298d7fc61148" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5ecf07d44cc5"><code>"2024-03-11T14:30:00Z"</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"13e564d9-7725-4a88-9bc0-f3ed2afd2b90" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3b547bd9cac2">UTC timestamp when the event was produced</p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3fa30154-1069-4d65-bf32-141cf3ae9083">
<td data-local-id=3D"f61d6979-38bc-44ab-8558-46d12e5ea819" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9c02801afad2"><code>source</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0198cc6a-fec5-4d09-8d8d-a43528a5d47c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b834773d65bc">string</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c042ccd4-70da-4ff0-ab5c-8e021f3728a9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"158a58d8e251">Yes =E2=80=94 set by producer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"448a431e-d8b9-476e-b000-c9174e90f947" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"73fecbe29a1c"><code>"kiosk"</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b3cfff40-5b85-4e16-94fa-6971c78fb256" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
