<td data-local-id=3D"7dfc1894-3b37-4111-a549-a6e9d848fde0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5f42178e425f">Version of the full message schema being used<=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"26d86c59-70cc-4a68-a02f-e51aee3492da">
<td data-local-id=3D"e54f3e1d-0013-4d4b-b40b-32a36b31ef6b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"849845444fc0"><code>payload</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9a6963e1-dede-4d84-8332-9ed84acd1a6f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a39ff9978935">object</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"37aa6f02-8083-4fbe-85bb-2b95f0f27610" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4780a038f8bb">Yes =E2=80=94 set by producer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3838518b-e40f-4c84-92ad-c542a3b7c20a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"40ed2b259bd1"><code>{...}</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1466e9db-b98d-4e8a-9b84-45cd1d8f182e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7abc4b8fbe6c">Domain-specific event data</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "eventId": "a1b2-c3d4-e5f6-g7h8",
  "eventVersion": "1.0.0",
  "timestamp": "2024-03-11T14:30:00Z",
  "source": "kiosk",
  "correlationId": "pricing.quote.requested-a1b2c3d4",
  "schemaVersion": "1.0.0",
  "payload": {
    "deviceId": "kiosk-12345",
    "transactionId": "txn-98765",
    "status": "completed"
  }
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"e87c859e3c8c"><code>eventId</code>, <code>eventVersion</code=
>, and <code>timestamp</code> are generated by MSK and do not need to be se=
t by the producer. <code>correlationId</code> must be set by the producer a=
nd carried forward across all related events to enable end-to-end tracing t=
hrough Datadog.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9404135dd46a"><strong>Event payload rules:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"9c56b56c-0582-4012-a6be-9a10e4d1fe06">
<li local-id=3D"a8d3276e-31ea-4192-a0ef-5431487fee3f">
<p local-id=3D"da9768ad50bf">Payloads must be <strong>JSON</strong>. Binary=
 serialization formats (Avro, Protobuf) are permitted for high-throughput M=
SK topics but should be discussed with Architecture before adoption.</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"2bae28ca-2357-4fc3-b9d1-770789e2d4b7">
<p local-id=3D"6d5bd97516cc">Events should carry <strong>enough context to =
be actionable</strong> without requiring the consumer to make additional AP=
I calls for the common case. Avoid purely notification-style events (just a=
n ID with no data) unless the payload would be prohibitively large. Prefer =
fat events over delta events.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"234d7bd0-f6f9-4306-9999-99b277fcb8f7">
<p local-id=3D"f1007706fc0f">Events should <strong>not</strong> carry sensi=
tive PII or credentials in the payload unless the topic/queue is encrypted =
at rest and access is appropriately restricted.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1176bce49f4a" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Eve=
ntVersioning">Event Versioning</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9770057a117b">Events use <code>eventVersion</code> to commun=
icate the version of the event schema, following SemVer (<code>MAJOR.MINOR.=
PATCH</code>).</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7c565dd6-a112-4861-9e5a-2af93e5f095b">
<li local-id=3D"2dd5e161-eb23-48d3-a67f-8201991fc433">
<p local-id=3D"850bf60cfea6">A <strong>breaking change</strong> =E2=80=94 f=
ield removal, type changes, renamed fields, semantic changes =E2=80=94 incr=
ements the major version. Consumers must be notified before a new major ver=
sion goes live.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c314940c-f3de-462e-bdff-c8095321f21a">
<p local-id=3D"d6512dc9f0af">A <strong>non-breaking change</strong> =E2=80=
=94 new optional fields =E2=80=94 increments the minor version.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"53c37f6d-74ff-41a8-99db-72b26b441afd">
<p local-id=3D"8d0075d1d5e3">Patch increments are reserved for documentatio=
n or metadata corrections with no payload impact.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2a87cbf7-c905-4bb5-8385-d9c5cf5181bf">
<p local-id=3D"ddd7a720ddc4">Deprecated versions must have a <strong>minimu=
m 3-month notice period</strong> before the producer stops publishing them.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e3461cec-e7ba-4bff-a2c0-801199720270">
<p local-id=3D"d85e96ed205f">Producers should publish both the old and new =
major version in parallel during the deprecation window.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"19584d5ab247" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Sch=
emaGovernance">Schema Governance</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e9924028f3b1">Event schemas must eventually be registered in=
 a <strong>schema registry</strong>. The schema registry is the source of t=
ruth for all event contracts =E2=80=94 the async equivalent of Stoplight fo=
r REST APIs.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"4c2689ad-b3e9-4adc-a707-8e9e9d79c834">
<li local-id=3D"8ba41f1d-693c-48fa-a9dd-bc0cebe3478c">
<p local-id=3D"e69bb057bf37"><strong>AWS Glue Schema Registry</strong> is t=
he standard for MSK workloads.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7e8fc07f-869a-49b4-a271-4b29e6ec02d9">
<p local-id=3D"d9578dcb6d9f">Schema Registry adoption follows a maturity mo=
del:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7f3776e8-dda7-4958-bd4b-2dd2518c9e2b">
<li local-id=3D"cf61c35a-b69f-4934-9d71-ed6d1b835b2e">
<p local-id=3D"e3d940ef743d"><strong>Crawl</strong> =E2=80=94 Schema Regist=
ry is optional. Raw JSON is acceptable for initial development. Teams shoul=
d be aware this state carries schema risk: a producer shipping a breaking c=
hange has no enforcement mechanism to catch it at the source.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"477059ce-9dd5-4e10-bcc9-084b26d5bb47">
<p local-id=3D"c30734966dbe"><strong>Walk</strong> =E2=80=94 Schema Registr=
y is required. Schemas must be versioned and enforced. Teams should move to=
 Walk as soon as the cluster is past initial development.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"f1ee9a5c-582a-40eb-815e-29395e29bf6b">
<p local-id=3D"0995cc88e5ac">Schema definitions must live in <strong>source=
 control</strong>. Registration must be <strong>automated via CI pipeline</=
strong> =E2=80=94 no manual registration is permitted in production.</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"90fa3c6d-147a-4e64-b3a2-2126c45c186f">
<p local-id=3D"3c0a4d87f5d1">Schemas must enforce <strong>backward compatib=
ility</strong> by default.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"198372b9ff15" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Rel=
iabilityPatterns">Reliability Patterns</h3>
<p local-id=3D"dfede66921b5">Async systems fail differently than synchronou=
s ones. The following patterns are required for all event-driven services:<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"76ad423d7a81"><strong>Dead-Letter Queues (DLQs):</strong> Ev=
ery SQS queue and every Lambda event source mapping must have a configured =
DLQ. Messages that fail processing after the configured retry attempts must=
 land in the DLQ =E2=80=94 not be silently dropped. DLQs must be monitored =
in Datadog with alerts on non-zero depth.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5161231f41df"><strong>Idempotency:</strong> Event consumers =
must be <strong>idempotent</strong> =E2=80=94 processing the same event mor=
e than once must produce the same result as processing it once. At-least-on=
ce delivery is the default guarantee for SQS and SNS. Consumers must use th=
e <code>eventId</code> field to detect and handle duplicates.</p>
<p local-id=3D"18d31b1e6652"><strong>Retry configuration:</strong> Configur=
e explicit retry policies on all event sources. Do not rely on defaults. Do=
cument the retry count and backoff strategy in the service's README.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0c1ac032448a"><strong>Poison pill handling:</strong> Consume=
rs must handle malformed or unprocessable messages gracefully =E2=80=94 log=
 the failure with full context, route to DLQ, and continue processing the r=
emaining batch. A single bad message must not block an entire queue. For re=
peat messages, consider idempotency and do not route to DLQ.</p>
<p local-id=3D"359f133cf2a6"><strong>Storage-first pattern (recommended for=
 critical flows):</strong> For high-criticality event flows, consumers shou=
ld persist the event to durable storage before acknowledging receipt, then =
process from storage. This provides an additional safety net beyond the DLQ=
 and enables replay without re-publishing.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"643ab3c1c145" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Obs=
ervabilityforAsyncSystems">Observability for Async Systems</h3>
<p local-id=3D"aa55172d12f9">Standard Datadog instrumentation applies to ev=
ent-driven services, with additional requirements:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"03d1fd20-511f-4c32-8bf2-56d957f51505">
<li local-id=3D"f29954ab-281f-4adf-b0f7-e8c22386b64b">
<p local-id=3D"9fc0828719a6">The <code><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker=
" data-ref=3D"41958050-b0d9-468e-8e33-ae87ea9308cb">correlationId</span></c=
ode><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"41958050-b0d9-468e-8e=
33-ae87ea9308cb"> </span>from the event envelope must be injected into Data=
dog traces on the consumer side to maintain end-to-end trace continuity acr=
oss async boundaries. Without this, async flows appear as broken or disconn=
ected traces.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b3a8c029-717a-41ab-90ae-1a0a37e6a94a">
<p local-id=3D"ee34948e70f4">DLQ depth must be a monitored metric with acti=
onable alerts. A non-zero DLQ is always a signal requiring investigation.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9bfee4b5-032e-4897-a057-29c8fb10aee3">
<p local-id=3D"fc2864603e42">Consumer lag must be tracked per consumer grou=
p in MSK and alerted on sustained lag above defined thresholds.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"15e7834d-be9f-4bc7-8832-0530b1f6352f">
<p local-id=3D"fcd6f817f5ad">Event publish failures must be logged and aler=
ted =E2=80=94 a producer that silently fails to publish is a silent data lo=
ss.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"db19a2d2-f428-418e-ac19-9e7e96653f5e">
<h2 local-id=3D"d5762fd58805" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Sec=
urityConsiderations">Security Considerations</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"0219091cdbe6" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Web=
ApplicationFirewall">Web Application Firewall</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d707a87c5e5c">All traffic <strong>must</strong> pass through=
 a top-level WAF, which is under the purview of the IT Security team.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b92c82ef954f" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-IAM=
Roles">IAM Roles</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9715ee88d518">Each application should have it=E2=80=99s own =
IAM role such that it is tailored to the permissions it needs.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"e7bac378d57e" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Aut=
hentication/Authorization">Authentication / Authorization</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4d2ece36d191">Authentication is handled at the top level by =
a <strong>custom Lambda Authorizer</strong> and Identity Provider. Both Ope=
nID Connect (Active Directory / internal SSO) and OAuth2 (AWS Cognito =E2=
=80=94 external users) are supported and authenticated against their issuer=
s as part of the auth flow.</p>
<p local-id=3D"90f2e27ad59a">For <strong>Machine-to-Machine (M2M)</strong> =
communication, the preference is <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:/=
/auth0.com/" rel=3D"nofollow">Auth0</a>. Applications may initially use Cog=
nito; the Authorizer supports both.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0d39c8259ad7">Bearer tokens are decoded to determine scopes =
and access to individual operations and endpoints. Access is enforced by ge=
nerating IAM policies based on decoded claims.</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"6086dafd-0831-476b-99f0-91f950eee36d">
<p local-id=3D"d087f0f6ec4f"><strong>=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F API keys must never=
 be used as an authentication scheme.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 local-id=3D"6ddc21477a21" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Sec=
retsManagement">Secrets Management</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2f63e35f4d9b">Hardcoded credentials of any kind are prohibit=
ed. All secrets, API keys, and connection strings must be stored in and ret=
rieved from <strong>AWS Secrets Manager</strong>. No secret values may be c=
ommitted to source control or embedded in application code or container ima=
ges.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"4c1d7460d492" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Enc=
ryptionRequirements">Encryption Requirements</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5a3fe51906a6"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"5ef32260-0895-41b0-b3ea-c664c234e5be">All traffic must be over </span><=
strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"5ef32260-0895-41b0=
-b3ea-c664c234e5be">HTTPS using TLS 1.3</span></strong><span class=3D"inlin=
e-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"5ef32260-0895-41b0-b3ea-c664c234e5be"> minimu=
m for new services. TLS 1.2 is permitted as a legacy carve-out for existing=
 integrations that cannot yet be upgraded. Any traffic over HTTP will be bl=
ocked outright.</span><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-re=
f=3D"5ef32260-0895-41b0-b3ea-c664c234e5be"> </span></strong><span class=3D"=
inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"5ef32260-0895-41b0-b3ea-c664c234e5be">Al=
l data should be encrypted at rest.</span></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"62508452d469" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Cro=
ss-OriginResourceSharing(CORS)">Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9f0384dcc6c4">All applications accessible via a frontend mus=
t have CORS enabled. The following settings are the minimum required:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"4=
66545fd-f4bb-4529-b471-4d64f68fc42a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"681dafd4-615a-470e-b360-746c712d45cf">
<th data-local-id=3D"b0f0407a-7f9a-4b60-b726-a6212db6af25" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"4c7e8447e958">Header</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e7977f92-51b6-444b-8ee4-5b96cbb8a97c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"eb765a3e3cf1">Requirement</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4f9a5626-4f1f-4b08-b894-1d17e140cd65">
<td data-local-id=3D"c8dc6975-3100-4374-9a86-970acea40bae" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"82a5c5d98c1c"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code></p></=
td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2f0be3a2-1009-468d-a6e3-7f8c3bfd8f74" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fba93268d6e1">Set to the specific sites that will access the=
 resource</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"25cfab2e-688a-4cb0-ae5f-ec4bbb767696">
<td data-local-id=3D"3e0ac950-f07b-4010-ad1b-26d686d25137" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d3b80979a92c"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Methods</code></p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8ddf768e-7faa-45d6-b14b-9c73a5919de6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"54cf9982171e">Set to the HTTP methods the resource supports;=
 always include <code>OPTIONS</code> (preflight)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"f418b6a0-c2d3-4480-9f54-c32f85cd6c2f">
<td data-local-id=3D"bc928421-9211-4ef3-94ef-04a4670d455e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8c7fcdde83d4"><code>Access-Control-Allow-Credentials</code><=
/p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0eb3607b-a341-4751-9fb6-68bb1fce8370" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"196d9a06bf69">Always <code>true</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"9501784af72c" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Eve=
ntSecurity">Event Security</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ff54d5fcb0ce">Event-driven systems have a distinct security =
surface from HTTP APIs:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"987cf3b6-3348-45de-a2ad-f8be4f17f471">
<li local-id=3D"801727f5-2703-4e9f-90c6-d7fe9818671e">
<p local-id=3D"93f55537184c"><strong>Topic/queue access control:</strong> I=
AM policies must restrict which services can publish to and consume from ea=
ch topic, queue, or event bus. Least-privilege applies =E2=80=94 a consumer=
 should not have publish rights, and a producer should not have consume rig=
hts on its own topics.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e19bb4ef-055c-4f1d-9c6d-0a5b87d86da2">
<p local-id=3D"1094c7a1627f"><strong>Payload sensitivity:</strong> Sensitiv=
e data (PII, credentials, payment data) must not be transmitted in event pa=
yloads unless the channel is encrypted at rest (all AWS managed services en=
crypt at rest by default) and access is tightly scoped. Consider referencin=
g a record by ID and having the consumer fetch the sensitive data via a sec=
ured API rather than embedding it in the event.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"feca78e10747" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Con=
tinuousSecurity">Continuous Security</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d13e4f27adf8">All Docker base images and package dependencie=
s (npm, pip, etc.) must pass a<strong> vulnerability scan tool</strong> in =
CI before deployment. Builds with critical or high severity findings must n=
ot be promoted to production without a documented exception approved by IT =
Security.</p>
<p local-id=3D"735df4a7e755">IT Security is evaluating additional tooling f=
or both build-time and run-time protection. This section will be updated as=
 those decisions are finalized.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b6429d0c8910" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Log=
ging">Logging</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5ec4ce471f73">PII should not be exposed in logs.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"5597ff40-1ece-477e-82f1-7b540994388f">
<h2 local-id=3D"a01dd1098273" id=3D"GoldenPath-WebMicroserviceFramework-Ref=
erences">References</h2>
